The workers' city, far below the
 surface of the earth.

3
00:05:23,957 --> 00:05:31,231
And high above, a pleasure garden for the sons of the masters of Metropolis.

4
00:05:37,137 --> 00:05:43,143
"Freder!"

5
00:07:24,111 --> 00:07:31,718
"Look, these are your brothers."

6
00:08:44,925 --> 00:08:47,194
"Who was that?"

7
00:08:52,065 --> 00:09:00,741
"Just the daughter of a worker."

8
00:09:11,985 --> 00:09:21,028
The great machines, far underground,
 yet high above the workers' city.

9
00:11:56,083 --> 00:11:59,186
"Moloch!"

10
00:17:35,188 --> 00:17:39,459
"Such acidents are unavoidable."

11
00:18:13,060 --> 00:18:20,667
"Why was my son allowed to go
 into the machine-rooms?"

12
00:18:37,985 --> 00:18:41,188
"Why did you go down there?"

13
00:18:43,123 --> 00:18:54,568
"I wanted to see what my brothers
 looked like."

14
00:20:22,756 --> 00:20:28,562
"It was their hands that built this
 city of ours, father."

15
00:21:02,929 --> 00:21:07,601
"In their proper place---
the depts."

16
00:21:26,219 --> 00:21:33,961
"What will you do if they turn against
 you some day?"

17
00:22:13,333 --> 00:22:20,107
"The foreman from the central dynamo 
room is here with an urgent message."

18
00:22:47,968 --> 00:22:54,274
"More of those plans, sir."

19
00:23:42,623 --> 00:23:49,329
"They were found on two of the men
 who were killed today."

20
00:24:05,045 --> 00:24:12,085
"Joseph, why was it not you who
 brought me these plans?"

21
00:24:39,146 --> 00:24:48,255
"You are dismissed. Go to the G-Bank 
for the balance of your wages."

22
00:25:44,177 --> 00:25:56,623
"Father, don't you realize what it 
means to be dismissed by you?"

23
00:27:11,932 --> 00:27:16,069
"Joseph, I need your help."

24
00:27:26,847 --> 00:27:34,688
"I have far to go today
-- alone, into the depths
-- to my borthers."

25
00:29:04,478 --> 00:29:09,383
"The machine! Someone must stay
 with the machine."

26
00:29:16,356 --> 00:29:20,060
"I will stay at the machine."

27
00:29:43,850 --> 00:29:50,090
In the middle of the city was an old house.

28
00:29:57,097 --> 00:30:02,569
Here lived, Rotwang, the inventor.

29
00:30:49,750 --> 00:30:53,720
"At last, my work is ready."

30
00:30:59,760 --> 00:31:07,935
"I have created a machine in the image
 of man, that never tires or makes a mistake."

31
00:31:23,150 --> 00:31:29,022
"Now we have no further use for
living workers."

32
00:34:08,048 --> 00:34:17,257
"Isn't it worth the loss of a hand to have 
created the workers of the future -- -- the machine men?"

33
